REMARK 280 CRYSTALLIZATION CONDITIONS: SARS-COV-2 MPRO WAS THAWED AND DILUTED   
REMARK 280 TO 6 MG/ML (USING 20 MM HEPES, PH 7.5, 50 MM NACL). BETA-LACTAM 20E  
REMARK 280 WAS ADDED TO THE PROTEIN SOLUTION TO A FINAL CONCENTRATION OF 10     
REMARK 280 MM; THE MIXTURE WAS INCUBATED FOR 2 H AT AMBIENT TEMPERATURE PRIOR   
REMARK 280 TO DISPENSING PLATES. THE DROP COMPOSITION WAS 0.15 UL PROTEIN       
REMARK 280 LIGAND SOLUTION, 0.3 UL 11 PERCENT V/V PEG 4000, 0.1 M MES, PH       
REMARK 280 6.5, AND 0.05 ,MICROL MPRO CRYSTAL SEED STOCK. THE MPRO CRYSTAL      
REMARK 280 SEED STOCK WAS PREPARED BY CRUSHING MPRO CRYSTALS WITH A PIPETTE     
REMARK 280 TIP, SUSPENDING THEM IN 30% PEG 4000, 5%V/V DMSO, 0.1 M MES PH 6.5,  
REMARK 280 AND VORTEXING FOR 60 S WITH APPROXIMATELY 10 GLASS BEADS (1.0 MM     
REMARK 280 DIAMETER, BIOSPEC PRODUCTS). AS RESERVOIR SOLUTION WAS USED: 11%V/   
REMARK 280 V PEG 4K, PH 6.5. CRYSTALS WERE GROWN USING THE SITTING DROP VAPOR   
REMARK 280 DIFFUSION METHOD AT 20 DEGREE C AND APPEARED WITHIN 24 H, REACHING   
REMARK 280 FULL SIZE WITHIN 36 H. CRYSTALS WERE LOOPED AFTER ONE WEEK., VAPOR   
REMARK 280 DIFFUSION, SITTING DROP, TEMPERATURE 293K                            
